{
  "texts": [
    "Recently, the concept of prompt problems was proposed as a paradigm shift in this field [8,39].",
    "BugSpotter uses LLMs to address a less-explored topic: the generation of debugging exercises.",
    "BugSpotter: Methodology and ToolThe BugSpotter tool aims to help students read and understand problem specifications, reason about buggy code, and design test cases that reveal bug(s).",
    "When interacting with BugSpotter, a student is shown a code debugging exercise, comprising a problem specification and a buggy code for the problem.",
    "To solve this, the student has to design a test case that will reveal the error in the code (see Figure 1)."
  ]
}